<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ancient2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ancient,</orth> subst. 1) the next in command under the lieutenant: <cit><quote>--s, corporals, lieutenants,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 2, 26</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a. Pistol</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.74" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 74</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.74" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 74</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.74" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 74</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.74" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 74</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 18</bibl> (Fluellen pronounces <emph>Aunchient</emph>). <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.2.49" default="NO" valid="yes">2, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.121" default="NO" valid="yes">3, 121</bibl> and passim. Fluellen says: <cit><quote>an aunchient lieutenant,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 13</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) standard: <cit><quote>an old faced a.,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 2, 34</bibl></cit>, an old standard mended with a different colour.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>